18:15.137 --> 18:18.772
- Okay.

18:18.840 --> 18:20.507
- You can tell your counsel

18:20.575 --> 18:22.876
He can avoid a lengthy
subpoena of all records

18:22.944 --> 18:24.178
If we get a list now

18:24.245 --> 18:28.782
Of all the people
attending those events.

18:28.850 --> 18:31.618
- You know,
most mid-level guys

18:31.686 --> 18:33.420
Who play
that glad-handing role

18:33.488 --> 18:35.188
Are people pleasers.

18:35.256 --> 18:37.657
You know, it's their job
to make everybody happy.

18:37.725 --> 18:39.893
They satisfy the clients.
They satisfy the boss.

18:39.961 --> 18:40.961
- Uh-huh.

18:41.028 --> 18:43.997
- He was, uh,
oddly empowered.

18:44.064 --> 18:46.099
- Good point.

18:46.167 --> 18:48.902
- Yeah, so, anyway,
how many on this list

18:48.969 --> 18:51.004
Had interaction with amber?

18:51.071 --> 18:52.238
[cell phone chirps]

18:52.306 --> 18:54.574
It's gonna take
some interview time.

18:54.641 --> 18:56.642
- Mm-hmm.
Oh, maybe not.

18:56.710 --> 19:00.046
Amber was picked up
in jersey city a half hour ago.

19:01.515 --> 19:04.116
- Look, I didn't even know
kevin was dead.

19:04.184 --> 19:05.651
- So why were you running?

19:05.719 --> 19:07.453
- I wasn't running.

19:07.521 --> 19:08.854
We had a fight.

19:08.922 --> 19:11.257
I left him. I was looking
for a new place to live.

19:11.324 --> 19:14.326
- With someone wealthy,
more desirable?

19:14.394 --> 19:16.929
We know you work
with sierra brandis.

19:16.996 --> 19:18.430
- So what?

19:18.498 --> 19:20.833
I was making good money.

19:20.900 --> 19:23.902
[scoffs] I didn't want kevin
screwing it up.

19:26.205 --> 19:28.907
We fought, I moved out--
simple as that.

19:28.975 --> 19:31.343
- And kevin was selling

19:31.411 --> 19:34.079
What you'd provided to him
to the tabloids

19:34.147 --> 19:36.014
And maybe using it
for blackmail.

19:36.082 --> 19:39.617
How'd you feel about that,
first of all?

19:39.685 --> 19:40.952
- Am I under arrest?

19:41.020 --> 19:43.788
- You're here
on a material-witness warrant.

19:43.856 --> 19:45.223
- So I can leave.
- You can.

19:45.290 --> 19:47.725
And you can return
under a murder warrant.

19:47.793 --> 19:49.827
We have options.

19:52.598 --> 19:54.432
- [scoffs]

19:54.499 --> 19:56.267
Okay.

19:58.270 --> 20:00.704
Kevin was trying to put
the squeeze on someone,

20:00.772 --> 20:02.739
A wall street bigwig--

20:02.807 --> 20:06.109
Married,
lots of money, great car,

20:06.177 --> 20:09.513
And some expensive
weird sexual preferences.

20:09.580 --> 20:11.748
- Weird?
Like what?

20:11.816 --> 20:14.684
- Dressing up,
combat makeup--

20:14.752 --> 20:16.820
I played
the terrified victim.

20:16.887 --> 20:18.888
Not something
he'd want to share

20:18.956 --> 20:20.623
With his friends
at the country club.

20:20.691 --> 20:22.625
- You have photos,
videotape, what?

20:22.693 --> 20:25.829
- [sighs]
kevin put a camera

20:25.896 --> 20:27.863
In a laptop computer.

20:27.931 --> 20:31.132
I'd set it up in the hotel room
and press record.

20:31.200 --> 20:34.101
- This wall street character--

20:34.169 --> 20:36.537
Amber,
we're gonna need a name.

20:38.740 --> 20:41.374
- [sighs]

20:41.442 --> 20:44.343
I can give you a name.

20:45.745 --> 20:48.247
[car door opens]

20:48.314 --> 20:51.716
- What's up?

20:51.784 --> 20:53.451
- You didn't return my calls.

20:53.519 --> 20:55.653
- I'm jammed up.

20:57.790 --> 21:01.360
You're gonna need a better ride
to go with that new office.

21:01.428 --> 21:03.496
Let's have breakfast
tomorrow.

21:03.564 --> 21:06.600
- Sure.

21:11.945 --> 21:14.947
[engine turning]

21:25.226 --> 21:26.827
- David?

21:26.895 --> 21:29.496
- Nathan trusts me
with his life.

21:29.564 --> 21:32.366
I need to know,
do you trust me too?

21:32.434 --> 21:35.336
- Of course I trust you.

21:35.404 --> 21:36.905
I love you.

21:39.642 --> 21:41.343
- Oh.

21:41.411 --> 21:43.479
I know. I know.

21:43.547 --> 21:45.949
[sobbing]

21:46.016 --> 21:49.019
- Something triggered
the dream and the sweats.

21:49.086 --> 21:50.921
What?

21:54.091 --> 21:56.059
- Nothing.
- No.

21:56.127 --> 21:58.461
We went through this
after you came back.

21:58.529 --> 22:00.096
You remember?
You remember how we talked?

22:00.164 --> 22:02.533
- Everything I do
is for us!

22:02.600 --> 22:04.435
Everything.

22:08.773 --> 22:10.707
[sniffles]

22:13.444 --> 22:16.279
Just believe me...

22:19.349 --> 22:22.517
Whatever happens,

22:22.585 --> 22:25.954
I need you so much.

22:34.791 --> 22:36.759
- I have no idea
what you're talking about.

22:36.827 --> 22:38.765
I hired models,
that's all.

22:38.833 --> 22:40.806
- And you sampled
the merchandise.

22:40.874 --> 22:41.842
- Excuse me?

22:41.909 --> 22:44.278
- Amber donelli,
that so-called model--

22:44.346 --> 22:46.783
We talked about her yesterday.
I-I showed you the picture.

22:46.851 --> 22:49.990
She claims that you and she
had a sexual relationship.

22:50.057 --> 22:51.958
- A sexual--no.

22:52.026 --> 22:53.760
You're wrong.
I'm a married man.

22:53.828 --> 22:55.862
- Well, I'm betting
most of the clients

22:55.930 --> 22:58.764
That use platinum encounters
are married too.

22:58.832 --> 23:00.365
- But amber donelli

23:00.433 --> 23:03.001
Does connect you
to kevin denaburg.

23:03.068 --> 23:04.736
- I told you,
I don't know him.

23:04.803 --> 23:06.437
- Kevin had pictures of you.

23:06.505 --> 23:07.839
Was he blackmailing you,
mr. Novak?

23:07.906 --> 23:09.940
- You don't have
to answer that, david.

23:10.008 --> 23:11.341
Nathan grayson.

23:11.409 --> 23:13.243
- I'm detective nichols.

23:13.310 --> 23:16.579
This is, uh, my partner,
detective stevens.

23:16.647 --> 23:18.514
- Look, I appreciate
that you have a job to do,

23:18.582 --> 23:20.551
But, uh, david
is entitled to counsel.

23:20.619 --> 23:22.218
- You're aware
of his association

23:22.286 --> 23:23.720
With high-end prostitutes?

23:23.787 --> 23:25.354
- I'm not.

23:25.422 --> 23:26.722
But from now on,

23:26.790 --> 23:28.957
I'll direct everything
through our company lawyer.

23:29.025 --> 23:30.625
David is an executive here.

23:30.693 --> 23:32.893
I will not have you
treat him this way.

23:32.961 --> 23:34.728
- Right,
you two served together.

23:34.796 --> 23:37.697
- Yes. We fought side by side
for this country.

23:37.765 --> 23:40.899
- So you know about his
less-than-honorable discharge.

23:40.967 --> 23:44.968
- Two unarmed civilians in iraq
shot to death.

23:45.036 --> 23:46.235
What happened there exactly?

23:46.303 --> 23:48.038
- Hey, people lied.
I was cleared.

23:48.105 --> 23:49.239
- David.
- I was not even charged.

23:49.307 --> 23:50.641
- Stop.

23:50.708 --> 23:53.643
You don't have to justify
anything to these people.

23:53.711 --> 23:55.044
Again, talk to our lawyer.

23:55.112 --> 23:57.180
Now, if you'll excuse us,
david has work,

23:57.248 --> 24:00.550
And I am late
for a luncheon.

24:10.161 --> 24:12.629
[door closes]

24:12.696 --> 24:14.096
- Hey, dad.
- Hi.

24:14.164 --> 24:16.032
- Good to see you.
- How are you?

24:16.099 --> 24:18.868
- Hey, sweetheart.
- Nice to see you.

24:18.936 --> 24:20.771
Shall we?

24:23.275 --> 24:26.377
- So union club?
- That sounds great.

24:26.445 --> 24:29.715
- Nice,
being one of the gods.

24:33.320 --> 24:36.322
- Nathan grayson
is a well-respected ceo.

24:36.390 --> 24:38.191
Do you really think
he's capable?

24:38.259 --> 24:40.860
- An ego-driven
power position like that?

24:40.928 --> 24:43.229
You know, it takes
a certain kind of narcissist

24:43.297 --> 24:44.964
To run a fortune 500.

24:45.032 --> 24:49.102
And amber donelli talked
about a bigwig wall street type

24:49.170 --> 24:51.804
With expensive kinky tastes.

24:51.872 --> 24:53.406
- David novak is low-level.

24:53.473 --> 24:54.941
Nathan grayson
has the real power.

24:55.008 --> 24:56.509
- Okay.

24:56.576 --> 24:57.844
You have a hunch,

24:57.911 --> 25:00.382
But it shouldn't take this
off of david novak.

25:00.449 --> 25:02.386
Find proof
he had sex with amber.

25:02.454 --> 25:04.291
- There's not one call,
text, or email.

25:04.359 --> 25:05.862
- Hey, you know
what I'm thinking?

25:05.929 --> 25:08.764
Kevin maybe
stalked her movements.

25:08.832 --> 25:09.765
- Hmm.

25:09.833 --> 25:12.100
- We have his cell phone.

25:13.669 --> 25:14.935
- Yeah.

25:15.003 --> 25:17.571
We'll do a gps trace,
check hotels in the area.

25:17.639 --> 25:20.240
- Good.

25:20.308 --> 25:22.375
- The doorman
at this midtown hotel

25:22.443 --> 25:24.478
Confirms david gave him
cash for rooms.

25:24.545 --> 25:27.649
- And about a week ago,
he's caught on tape

25:27.717 --> 25:30.052
With--watch this.

25:30.120 --> 25:32.455
That's kevin denaburg.

25:32.523 --> 25:35.293
- Okay, amber's testimony
plus this?

25:35.360 --> 25:37.596
Time for the d.A.

25:37.663 --> 25:39.664
- Well...

25:39.732 --> 25:41.264
- Am I sensing hesitation?

25:41.332 --> 25:44.733
- Look, david doesn't put up
any kind of fight.

25:44.801 --> 25:47.069
He's an iraq war veteran,

25:47.136 --> 25:48.403
Two tours.

25:48.471 --> 25:52.174
We talk to him,
he's tense, on edge.

25:52.242 --> 25:56.246
But when kevin
attacks him right here,

25:56.314 --> 25:59.048
He doesn't turn violent.

25:59.116 --> 26:02.684
- Unless he saved
the best for last--

26:02.752 --> 26:07.088
Sawing off kevin's head,
hands, and feet.

26:07.156 --> 26:09.956
- That may be true.

26:13.122 --> 26:14.586
[children chattering]

26:14.654 --> 26:16.254
- Let's go, guys.

26:16.321 --> 26:18.189
You got your presents?
- Yeah.

26:18.257 --> 26:19.590
[siren wails]

26:19.658 --> 26:22.093
- Hold on. Hold on.
- What's that?

26:22.161 --> 26:24.830
- Come here.
Come here.

26:24.898 --> 26:27.767
- David, what in the world?
- I'll deal with it.

26:32.071 --> 26:34.838
- Please, I'm taking my kids
to a birthday party.

26:34.906 --> 26:36.073
- It doesn't work
that way, david.

26:36.140 --> 26:38.408
Open the, uh, back
of your car, please.

26:38.476 --> 26:40.676
- No, not in front
of my kids.

26:40.744 --> 26:43.378
- I'll take them.
- Dad, what's happening?

26:43.446 --> 26:45.913
- Cynthia, wait.

26:45.981 --> 26:48.448
- Amber calls this
a great car?

26:48.516 --> 26:52.017
- Open the back
of your car, mr. Novak.

26:56.921 --> 26:58.188
It's clean.

26:58.256 --> 27:02.490
- It's too clean.
This liner has been replaced.

27:02.558 --> 27:04.358
We need to impound your car.

27:04.425 --> 27:07.594
- And we're gonna conduct
a full search of your home.

27:07.661 --> 27:10.897
- This is all wrong.

27:34.835 --> 27:37.335
- Shape and size
of the blade is similar.

27:37.402 --> 27:40.571
Bag and send
to forensics a.S.A.P.

27:40.639 --> 27:43.874
I think we got
enough here to arrest.

27:48.613 --> 27:50.714
- We're good.

27:53.484 --> 27:55.351
- You need to stay back,
mrs. Novak.

27:55.419 --> 27:57.352
- Please, he's my husband.

27:57.420 --> 28:00.354
- We'll be okay.
I promise.

28:03.356 --> 28:04.856
- This is devastating.

28:04.924 --> 28:07.359
I mean, david is not
just an employee.

28:07.426 --> 28:09.494
He's--he's a friend.

28:09.561 --> 28:11.395
- So you knew
about the prostitutes?

28:11.463 --> 28:13.664
- No, not--
not really knew.

28:13.732 --> 28:16.433
You know, but--
but people work long hours.

28:16.501 --> 28:18.968
It's stressful.

28:19.036 --> 28:20.302
Some need to play.

28:20.370 --> 28:23.204
- You ever play,
mr. Grayson?

28:23.272 --> 28:26.473
- I resent that, detective.
This is about david, not me.

28:26.541 --> 28:28.975
Let's move on to areas
that can be more helpful.

28:29.042 --> 28:31.310
- Yeah, that's
what we're looking for--

28:31.377 --> 28:33.144
Always helpful.

28:33.212 --> 28:34.579
So in that vein,

28:34.647 --> 28:36.880
Can you tell us more
about your relationship

28:36.948 --> 28:38.181
With your friend david?

28:38.249 --> 28:40.183
Back in iraq,

28:40.251 --> 28:43.218
Any problems
when you guys served together?

28:43.286 --> 28:44.820
- I always believed in him,

28:44.887 --> 28:47.689
Even after his trouble
over there.

28:47.756 --> 28:49.156
- The dead civilians.

28:49.224 --> 28:51.958
- Nobody believed
those iraqi witnesses.

28:52.026 --> 28:54.794
Even my father weighed in
with his connections

28:54.862 --> 28:56.129
To help david out.

28:56.197 --> 28:57.997
- And what were david's duties
here at the bank?

28:58.065 --> 28:59.932
- David's easy to like.

29:00.000 --> 29:02.100
He's good
with clients, so...

29:02.168 --> 29:03.501
- Yeah, planning parties

29:03.569 --> 29:05.837
And showing clients
a good time--

29:05.905 --> 29:07.338
That's what
brought him in contact

29:07.406 --> 29:10.442
With the murder victim, huh?

29:10.510 --> 29:12.344
The boyfriend
of one of the prostitutes

29:12.412 --> 29:14.179
With whom he was consorting.

29:14.247 --> 29:18.749
- You seem to know
a good deal more than I do.

29:18.817 --> 29:20.851
Uh, look, detectives,

29:20.919 --> 29:24.021
I want to be helpful
putting this behind us,

29:24.088 --> 29:26.690
But, uh, unfortunately,
right now...

29:26.758 --> 29:28.425
I'm late for a meeting,

29:28.493 --> 29:31.094
So if--if you don't mind...

29:32.596 --> 29:34.797
- Yeah, sure.
Absolutely.

29:34.865 --> 29:38.200
You have been,
in fact, very helpful.

29:38.268 --> 29:39.769
We'll be in touch.

29:42.840 --> 29:44.240
- He means that.

29:51.080 --> 29:53.147
My guess is
the last thing he needs

29:53.215 --> 29:55.282
Is a scandal
with some prostitute.

29:55.350 --> 29:57.551
Throwing david under the bus
makes a certain sense.

29:57.619 --> 29:58.885
- Yeah, what he's
really trying to avoid

29:58.953 --> 30:01.654
Is a bigger scandal--
killing kevin denaburg.

30:01.722 --> 30:03.222
- Well, it's still a leap,

30:03.290 --> 30:04.923
Given the mountain of evidence
against david.

30:04.991 --> 30:06.325
- Wait. Wait.

30:06.392 --> 30:10.463
David, in iraq, is accused
of killing unarmed civilians,

30:10.531 --> 30:13.572
But nathan grayson's father
puts his reputation on the line

30:13.639 --> 30:14.807
For a guy he's never met?

30:14.875 --> 30:17.576
- There's an expression,
"bleeding army green"--

30:17.644 --> 30:19.745
What you'll do
for the men you serve with.

30:19.813 --> 30:23.082
- Or what a father'll do
for family, for his son.

30:23.150 --> 30:25.351
- With all
we're putting david through,

30:25.419 --> 30:26.619
I hope you're wrong.

30:26.687 --> 30:28.454
- 'cause if I'm right,

30:28.522 --> 30:31.023
We're charging the wrong guy
with murder.

30:34.477 --> 30:36.244
- Aren't you supposed
to build cases

30:36.312 --> 30:37.546
And not take them apart?

30:37.614 --> 30:39.248
- I just think
it's a very strong possibility

30:39.316 --> 30:40.817
That david
is covering for nathan.

30:40.884 --> 30:43.318
- I can't go to the d.A.
With that.

30:43.385 --> 30:44.419
- Well, there's also the car

30:44.486 --> 30:46.254
That amber described
as "a great car."

30:46.321 --> 30:48.522
- Which doesn't fit
david's suv.

30:48.590 --> 30:51.124
- So maybe he rented
a ferrari to impress her.

30:51.192 --> 30:52.926
It still doesn't link
nathan grayson

30:52.993 --> 30:54.961
To the killing
of kevin denaburg.

30:55.028 --> 30:56.929
- Here, will this help?

30:56.997 --> 30:58.597
Take a look at those.

31:03.269 --> 31:05.069
- It might mean complicity,

31:05.137 --> 31:06.904
But blood from the victim

31:06.971 --> 31:10.874
Matches samples found
on david's saw and in his car.

31:10.941 --> 31:12.575
- Because he dealt
with the body,

31:12.643 --> 31:13.909
But that's all he did.

31:13.977 --> 31:15.578
The murder weapon
was a car door.

31:15.646 --> 31:17.914
The wounds on kevin denaburg

31:17.981 --> 31:19.882
Don't match the measurements

31:19.949 --> 31:24.287
Of the toyotas that are driven
by david or s wife.

31:26.624 --> 31:28.291
- And nathan grayson?

31:28.359 --> 31:31.360
- Registration shows
that he has an s-class mercedes,

31:31.428 --> 31:33.363
Which a jersey girl
like amber donelli

31:33.431 --> 31:35.832
Could describe
as a great car.

31:35.900 --> 31:37.233
- You're asking me to act

31:37.301 --> 31:39.201
On a vague piece
of circumstantial evidence.

31:39.269 --> 31:40.969
- We think
it's more than that.

31:41.037 --> 31:44.939
- I don't often give orders,
but you both know the problem.

31:45.007 --> 31:47.742
You stay away from david novak
and his lawyer.

31:47.810 --> 31:49.744
Your theory could provide
an alternate theory

31:49.811 --> 31:50.945
For david's defense,

31:51.013 --> 31:53.881
And if he's guilty,
he could go free.

31:56.518 --> 31:58.419
- Detective stevens?
- Mm-hmm?

31:58.487 --> 32:00.255
- Detective, uh...

32:00.322 --> 32:02.257
You know military
legal procedure, yes?

32:02.325 --> 32:03.925
- What, the ucmj?

32:03.992 --> 32:06.622
My--my father wasn't
in the judge advocate's office.

32:06.690 --> 32:07.990
- From what I know,

32:08.058 --> 32:10.126
It's very hard to make
a military murder case

32:10.193 --> 32:11.428
Without a body.

32:11.495 --> 32:14.031
- I grew up learning
how much they like hard facts.

32:14.098 --> 32:16.367
- At the time this happened,
do you remember?

32:16.435 --> 32:18.269
Terror killings
were rampant.

32:18.337 --> 32:20.270
Civilians murdered
by death squads,

32:20.338 --> 32:21.872
Even corrupt police--
you remember that?

32:21.939 --> 32:23.573
- Yeah, there were
mass graves everywhere,

32:23.641 --> 32:24.841
Bodies strewn.

32:24.909 --> 32:27.042
- Bodies whose
heads and hands and feet

32:27.110 --> 32:29.244
Had been cut off.

32:29.312 --> 32:31.813
- To hide their identity...
- Yeah.

32:31.881 --> 32:33.315
- Like our victim.

32:33.383 --> 32:34.850
- That's right.

32:34.917 --> 32:37.853
- Yeah, but that--that points
towards david's guilt,

32:37.921 --> 32:39.254
Not his innocence.

32:39.322 --> 32:40.722
- David moved the body,

32:40.790 --> 32:42.757
And he cut it up just like
he'd done before in iraq,

32:42.825 --> 32:45.727
For nathan.

32:45.795 --> 32:50.065
- We can't go and speak
to david about this.

32:50.132 --> 32:51.400
- That's okay.

32:51.467 --> 32:53.902
I'd rather talk to the wife.

32:53.969 --> 32:55.069
- Okay.

32:55.137 --> 32:57.572
[chuckles]
but you heard callas in there.

32:57.639 --> 33:01.075
There's a line
we can't cross.

33:01.143 --> 33:03.678
- What, are you kidding?
- No, I'm not kidding.

33:03.745 --> 33:07.682
You go there, I'll--
I'll terminate the interview.

33:07.749 --> 33:11.018
- Your father
only wanted facts.

33:11.086 --> 33:14.788
My mother taught me to work
within boundaries.

33:18.226 --> 33:20.828
- His prior job
was claims adjuster.

33:20.895 --> 33:22.796
When he got called up
by the reserve,

33:22.864 --> 33:26.099
Our world collapsed,
financially.

33:26.166 --> 33:29.369
- Since then, you seem
to have done pretty well.

33:29.437 --> 33:31.372
- Yeah, we have...

33:31.440 --> 33:33.007
Until now.

33:33.074 --> 33:35.609
But look,
my husband is innocent.

33:35.677 --> 33:38.045
He's not a killer.
He is a good man.

33:38.113 --> 33:39.780
- Nathan grayson...

33:39.848 --> 33:41.716
Isn't a great deal
owed to him?

33:41.783 --> 33:43.617
- What we have
comes from david's hard work,

33:43.685 --> 33:45.219
Not nathan's favors.

33:45.287 --> 33:47.454
- A cushy job
at the bank.

33:47.521 --> 33:50.056
Why do you suppose
nathan gave him that?

33:50.124 --> 33:51.758
- They became close in iraq.

33:51.826 --> 33:54.961
What those guys went through,
nobody can understand.

33:55.029 --> 33:58.064
Those iraqis were always
accusing our servicemen.

33:58.132 --> 33:59.432
The so-called witnesses

33:59.500 --> 34:01.401
Couldn't even pick david
out of a lineup!

34:01.469 --> 34:03.336
- Cynthia...

34:03.404 --> 34:05.972
It's possible
that those witnesses

34:06.040 --> 34:08.574
Didn't see david
doing the crime,

34:08.641 --> 34:10.909
But somebody that david knew.

34:13.013 --> 34:14.746
- I don't understand.

34:14.815 --> 34:16.349
- Well, think about it.

34:16.416 --> 34:19.585
Nathan swoops in
as soon as they come back

34:19.652 --> 34:22.522
And sets him up at the bank.

34:24.591 --> 34:26.525
- Oh, my god.

34:26.592 --> 34:28.527
Nathan?

34:28.596 --> 34:30.797
He took the blame
for nathan?

34:37.701 --> 34:40.203
We'd lost our house.

34:40.271 --> 34:42.272
He was coming back
to no job,

34:42.340 --> 34:44.373
Marked by
a general discharge,

34:44.442 --> 34:46.777
And then everything
suddenly turned around.

34:46.844 --> 34:48.344
- Because of nathan.

34:48.413 --> 34:50.914
- Oh.
[scoffs]

34:50.982 --> 34:53.817
And david thinks nathan
cares about him.

35:00.858 --> 35:03.159
- Mr. Grayson...

35:03.227 --> 35:04.994
Thank you so much
for coming in.

35:05.062 --> 35:07.630
Our captain agreed
that it's, uh, very important

35:07.698 --> 35:09.031
For you to be
part of this process.

35:09.099 --> 35:10.433
Thank you.

35:10.500 --> 35:12.868
- Yeah, well, I'm relieved
to hear somebody listens.

35:12.936 --> 35:14.537
- Yeah.
Fair warning, though--

35:14.604 --> 35:18.007
David's defense is undoubtedly
gonna subpoena you

35:18.075 --> 35:19.408
And try to confuse
the jury about--

35:19.476 --> 35:23.011
- He's actually asked me
for defense counsel.

35:23.079 --> 35:24.512
- Really?

35:24.580 --> 35:26.180
And what, you're gonna--
you're gonna take

35:26.248 --> 35:28.816
A "wait and see" attitude
on that?

35:28.884 --> 35:31.252
Oh, that's
a very smart move.

35:31.320 --> 35:33.687
- Detective,
I was harvard law.

35:33.755 --> 35:36.958
I could teach
courtroom strategy to your d.A.

35:40.396 --> 35:42.464
- Please.

35:46.135 --> 35:47.769
- Wh--what's this?

35:47.837 --> 35:51.139
- Take it easy. We're just gonna
sort some things out--

35:51.207 --> 35:53.508
The details of kevin's death.

35:53.576 --> 35:55.377
- I don't know
anything about that.

35:55.445 --> 35:57.212
- You meet him up in yonkers.

35:57.280 --> 35:59.648
- No.
No, no, I didn't.

35:59.715 --> 36:01.182
- We know you were there.

36:01.250 --> 36:03.085
The gps reading on your car
tells us so.

36:03.153 --> 36:04.957
- Bull.
There's nothing on my system.

36:05.025 --> 36:06.759
- Well, you erased the entry
from your system,

36:06.827 --> 36:08.428
But your gps provider,

36:08.496 --> 36:11.965
They--they store a backup
on their mainframe.

36:15.570 --> 36:19.672
So there's only one thing
we don't get.

36:19.740 --> 36:22.941
We know you used the highlander
to dump the body,

36:23.008 --> 36:26.210
But who was driving
the mercedes?

36:26.277 --> 36:28.111
David?

36:28.179 --> 36:30.713
You're going to jail.

36:30.781 --> 36:32.515
Would you like it to be
for a long time

36:32.582 --> 36:34.717
Or a really long time?

36:34.784 --> 36:37.853
Who drove the other car--
your wife?

36:37.921 --> 36:40.255
She help you?
- Keep my family out of this.

36:40.323 --> 36:41.857
- We talked to her.

36:41.925 --> 36:44.393
She seems
very committed to you.

36:44.461 --> 36:46.228
Seems like she'd do anything
to help you out.

36:46.296 --> 36:48.831
- Enough.
You can't mess with me.

36:48.899 --> 36:50.366
He called--
he called me in a panic.

36:50.433 --> 36:52.802
He said he'd take care of me,
take care of my family.

36:52.869 --> 36:54.303
- I did take care of you.

36:54.371 --> 36:55.537
- You son of a bitch.

36:55.605 --> 36:58.040
I won't let you do this to me,
not anymore!

36:58.107 --> 37:00.976
- David, it won't help you
to alienate me.

37:01.044 --> 37:04.813
- [breathing heavily]

37:12.688 --> 37:15.657
- But you do own a mercedes,

37:15.725 --> 37:18.393
Don't you, mr. Grayson?

37:18.461 --> 37:20.228
- Excuse me?

37:20.296 --> 37:22.864
- S-class, to be exact.

37:22.932 --> 37:24.666
- What does that have to do
with anything?

37:24.733 --> 37:28.569
- Maybe nothing,
possibly everything.

37:30.239 --> 37:31.973
- [chuckles]

37:32.041 --> 37:34.442
Forgive me, detective.

37:34.510 --> 37:36.511
It took me a few minutes
to catch on.

37:36.578 --> 37:40.648
This is quite a interesting
little game you're playing here.

37:40.716 --> 37:41.749
- What do you mean?

37:41.817 --> 37:44.185
- Yeah.

37:44.253 --> 37:47.488
Do us a favor, huh?
Lose the performance.

37:47.556 --> 37:49.523
If he's your star witness,

37:49.591 --> 37:52.059
Your case is already
in the toilet.

37:52.127 --> 37:54.094
- I wouldn't be so sure.

37:54.162 --> 37:58.465
Your flaw is that
you exploit people...

37:58.533 --> 37:59.833
Like david,

37:59.901 --> 38:03.103
'cause you're too weak
to face consequences.

38:03.171 --> 38:05.973
You come up against
a real crisis on your own,

38:06.040 --> 38:08.241
You fold.

38:08.309 --> 38:11.144
You're a coward.

38:11.212 --> 38:15.615
Yeah, amber donelli
called her sex client

38:15.683 --> 38:18.986
By the name david novak,

38:19.053 --> 38:21.889
But, uh,
here in these pictures,

38:21.957 --> 38:25.292

I don't care
what you told her your name was,

38:25.360 --> 38:28.559
That's you, nathan.

38:28.627 --> 38:30.992
Not the kind of thing

38:31.059 --> 38:34.129
That you'd, uh,
want around.

38:34.196 --> 38:37.066
- Ah.
Look at this--

38:37.134 --> 38:40.636
Using david's name,
letting him take the fall.

38:40.704 --> 38:42.938
You almost skated on this.

38:43.006 --> 38:45.040
- First in iraq,
now this.

38:45.108 --> 38:47.976
- You don't know anything.
- We know enough.

38:48.044 --> 38:49.645
- Nothing said here
is of any value.

38:49.712 --> 38:50.746
- Right.

38:50.813 --> 38:53.314
This has all been
just a little something

38:53.382 --> 38:57.351
To keep you occupied
while we searched your car.

38:57.419 --> 38:59.353
- You touch my car
without a warrant,

38:59.421 --> 39:01.322
And you will regret it,
I assure you.

39:01.389 --> 39:04.058
- Why? What are you gonna do--
call daddy?

39:04.125 --> 39:06.126
Huh?

39:06.194 --> 39:08.996
Here. He may, in fact, be
very interested in this.

39:09.063 --> 39:12.132
Come on in.
Thank you, jim.

39:12.200 --> 39:14.401
Mr. Grayson,
are you, uh, familiar

39:14.469 --> 39:17.004
With the mechanics
of door latches

39:17.072 --> 39:18.539
For various vehicles?

39:18.606 --> 39:20.007
- Enlighten me, please.

39:20.074 --> 39:22.242
- Well, each make
and model is unique.

39:22.310 --> 39:25.612
- Which makes
identification real easy.

39:25.680 --> 39:27.913
No two doorjambs are alike.

39:27.980 --> 39:30.446
- So let me understand this.

39:30.513 --> 39:33.414
You sandbagged me
with this circus act

39:33.482 --> 39:35.148
While you seized my car?

39:35.216 --> 39:38.216
- Uh-huh. We needed
to match the wound patterns

39:38.284 --> 39:39.983
From kevin's body
with your car door.

39:40.051 --> 39:42.048
- Well, since your stupidity

39:42.116 --> 39:44.048
Prevents you
from the realization

39:44.116 --> 39:45.883
Of your misguided actions,

39:45.950 --> 39:47.217
I'll explain.

39:47.285 --> 39:49.419
- Stupidity?
- Yeah.

39:49.487 --> 39:52.089
See, you had
no probable cause.

39:52.157 --> 39:53.390
Huh?

39:53.458 --> 39:57.460
So therefore your search
of my vehicle was illegal.

39:57.527 --> 40:00.629
Okay? You found the kid's
dna on my car door?

40:00.697 --> 40:04.766
So what? In the law, it's called
fruit of the poisoned tree.

40:04.834 --> 40:08.336
All evidence seized
during that search

40:08.403 --> 40:11.372
Is inadmissible.

40:11.439 --> 40:15.008
You just gave away
your entire case, detectives.

40:15.076 --> 40:17.512
- It's interesting
that you just talked

40:17.579 --> 40:20.215
About kevin getting hit
with a car door.

40:20.282 --> 40:22.351
David didn't know that.

40:22.419 --> 40:24.654
In effect,
what you've just told us

40:24.722 --> 40:27.691
Is that at the moment
that kevin was killed,

40:27.759 --> 40:29.594
David wasn't there.

40:29.661 --> 40:31.929
- As for your car,
it's right where you left it.

40:31.997 --> 40:34.198
A dealership on 41st street
lent us this.

40:34.266 --> 40:36.867
[clattering]
they were very helpful.

40:36.935 --> 40:39.070
- It's not your car.

40:39.138 --> 40:41.439
And you're right.

40:41.507 --> 40:43.874
We do need probable cause...

40:43.942 --> 40:45.710
To check your gps

40:45.777 --> 40:49.213
And the real car door
with the actual dna.

40:49.281 --> 40:52.549
But luckily, what you said...

40:52.617 --> 40:55.653
Just gave that to us.

40:55.720 --> 40:58.255
- After all I did...

40:58.323 --> 41:02.292
You keep these pictures
to screw me!

41:03.728 --> 41:06.830
- I trusted you...

41:06.898 --> 41:08.065
But not enough.

41:08.133 --> 41:10.500
I had to have
my insurance too.

41:10.568 --> 41:11.968
[handcuffs clicking]

41:12.036 --> 41:13.337
- Nathan grayson,

41:13.404 --> 41:15.706
You're under arrest for
the murder of kevin denaburg.

41:15.774 --> 41:17.441
- [spits]

41:17.509 --> 41:19.009
- You have the right
to remain silent.

41:19.077 --> 41:21.012
Anything you say can
and will be used against you

41:21.079 --> 41:22.180
In a court of law.

41:22.248 --> 41:24.583
You have the right
to an attorney...

41:37.028 --> 41:38.828
- Accessory after the fact.

41:38.895 --> 41:42.097
With a plea,
david's looking at some time.

41:43.934 --> 41:45.868
- I think she'll wait.

41:45.935 --> 41:47.069
- David...

41:47.137 --> 41:49.171
- He'll have nothing
when he comes out.

41:49.239 --> 41:51.373
- He'll have a conscience.

41:51.441 --> 41:53.175
She values that.

